    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Relatively small pencil-shaped instruments with a hard point, often metal or bone, used for marking, writing, or drawing. Among uses for styluses are for incising lines on a soft surface such as wax, for transferring drawings through tracing with pressure, with inked ribbon as a tracing-point in devices such as a seismograph or telegraph receiver, and as an indicator on touch-sensitive electronic devices.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
